ter 2 / Organizing</span><hr size=1> Gwelanna stood next and spoke &quot; My lords , and fellow lady &quot; Gwelanna nodded at Dyra the gnome queen. &quot; I implore you let me leave now so that I may speak with my superiors.&quot;<br>
<br>
Duke Balyn swallowed the rest of the brandy * I better stop or I'm going to fall of the damn podium *. &quot; I think it would be best if we all left right now. This will take months to get the army together and time is precious.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot; Duke Balyn &quot; Gwelanna interuppted &quot; One thousand spellcasters can move this army in a span of time less than two weeks , I can personally send all these delegates back home right now except for the dwarves , I have not been to their homelands. After I send the delegates home they can begin organizing their forces that are being sent and they can ready their forces and provisions. In two days I can have most of them here and in six days we can be ready to teleport to within a hundred miles of the dwarven mountains of King Ungar.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot; Thats sounds very damn good Lady Gwelanna , we'll have the bastards by the hair on their...&quot; Lord Koisur blurted. &quot;  by the hair on their head is what I was going to say &quot; Lord Koisur stammered.<br>
<br>
The council burst into laughter.<br>
<br>
Seven days later.<br>
<br>
Koisur and Dorin stood with the other leaders atop Duke Balyns citadel looking at the neat columns that the Coalition army made.<br>
<br>
&quot; Lady Gwelanna we owe you a great many favors , I believe that you will go down in history as a dwarven savior. &quot; Dorin said looking up at her.<br>
<br>
&quot; My Lord &quot; she began <br>
<br>
&quot; Just Dorin , I find that many people these days hate using titles &quot; Dorin interuppted.<br>
<br>
&quot; Dorin , I imagine you people would do the same for us , We do this because they are a common enemy and we need to Vanquish them all.&quot; Gwelanna finished.<br>
<br>
&quot; We would try and do the same for you , but I don't think we could reach your floating Island Gwel. &quot; said Koisur.<br>
<br>
Most of the new council members were here now atop Duke Balyns ramparts.<br>
<br>
&quot; ah Sir Garalad , your ten thousand cavalry will help greatly when we sink our teeth into the enemies flanks , Ohh.... I did not know you are Half-Elf?&quot; Koisur said with a perplexed look.<br>
<br>
&quot; Ohh that yes , well Humans and Elves accept us for brothers. Yes though ten thousand men and half-elves armed with lances and light plate armor make a very reliable medium cavalry, light enough to harass the enemy heavy enough to break them.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot; That Is music to my ears Garalad &quot; Koisur said with a large grin upon his weather beat face.<br>
<br>
Duke Balyn was Conversing with , Isithranil , Isil-Gawiel , Belil-Galinde , Elondil , and Sadriendir.<br>
&quot; The Kalefi elves are the best scouts in the world , with our elvish eyesight , speed , and deftness of body we can move anywhere unheard , however the Authofe elves are much better bowmen , still though , the ability to walk up to a deer without being heard is a grand ability.&quot;  bragged Belil-Galinde , Sadriendir nodded with agreement.<br>
<br>
Everyone was discussing strategy and plans of battle.<br>
<br>
Meanwhile The Demidemon leader of the evil races was leading well over 2 million creatures to capture the dwarven homelands and equip his army with armor.<br>
<br>
